## 9. Accessibility & Responsiveness

### 9.1 Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

**Requirements**:
- ✅ Color contrast ratio ≥4.5:1 (text on background)
- ✅ Keyboard navigation (all interactive elements)
- ✅ Screen reader support (ARIA labels)
- ✅ Focus indicators (visible outlines)
- ✅ Alt text for images (shields, crosses, badges)

**Implementation**:
```jsx
// Example: Accessible button
<button 
  className="btn-primary"
  aria-label="Connect MetaMask wallet to join VFIDE"
  tabIndex={0}
>
  🦊 Connect MetaMask
</button>
```

---

### 9.2 Responsive Design

**Breakpoints**:
- **Mobile**: 320px - 768px (80% of traffic)
- **Tablet**: 769px - 1024px
- **Desktop**: 1025px+ (target)

**Mobile Optimizations**:
- Collapse navigation to hamburger menu (Templar cross icon)
- Stack cards vertically
- Simplify 3D effects (disable Three.js on mobile, use static images)
- Touch-friendly buttons (min 44px × 44px)

**Example**:
```css
/* Desktop: 3D Templar cross */
@media (min-width: 1025px) {
  .templar-hero {
    background: url('/3d-cross-scene.webp');
  }
}

/* Mobile: Static image */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .templar-hero {
    background: url('/templar-cross-2d.webp');
  }
}
```

